No. She worked at a temp agency,
so she just had jobs here and there.

144
00:12:34,934 --> 00:12:37,459
She must have had someone
that she forgot to list.

145
00:12:37,536 --> 00:12:40,733
Try her high school.
Everyone has friends from high school.

146
00:12:40,806 --> 00:12:42,330
No, they don't.

147
00:12:42,408 --> 00:12:45,275
Maybe they have people they talk to,
or do things with...

148
00:12:45,344 --> 00:12:47,278
but they're not really friends.

149
00:12:47,346 --> 00:12:49,109
They're just filler.

150
00:12:51,450 --> 00:12:53,042
What? It's true.

151
00:12:54,253 --> 00:12:56,153
I want a glass of wine.

152
00:12:56,389 --> 00:12:57,617
Oh, God.

153
00:12:58,024 --> 00:12:59,514
It's so weird.

154
00:13:00,526 --> 00:13:02,756
Who the hell was Emily Previn?

155
00:13:05,131 --> 00:13:06,723
Nate, are you okay?

156
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:10,833
- Yeah, I'm fine.
- 'Cause your eyes look really weird.

157
00:13:11,203 --> 00:13:15,833
Yeah, it's just this medication I'm taking.
It makes me a little drowsy. That's all.

158
00:13:16,876 --> 00:13:18,138
Honestly.

159
00:13:22,581 --> 00:13:24,913
Maybe Emily Previn was autistic.

160
00:13:24,984 --> 00:13:29,853
I read an article about a high-functioning
autistic person who didn't need people.

161
00:13:29,922 --> 00:13:33,221
